Impute Ages Based on Affection Status and Sex

Source: R/imputeAges.R
imputeAges.Rd

This function imputes ages for individuals in a dataset based on their affection status and sex using either Weibull, baseline, or empirical distribution.

Usage

imputeAges(
  data,
  na_indices,
  baseline_male,
  baseline_female,
  alpha_male,
  beta_male,
  delta_male,
  alpha_female,
  beta_female,
  delta_female,
  empirical_density,
  max_age
)

Arguments

data

A data frame containing the data.

na_indices

A vector of indices indicating the rows in the data where ages need to be imputed.

baseline_male

A data frame containing baseline data for males.

baseline_female

A data frame containing baseline data for females.

alpha_male

Shape parameter for the Weibull distribution for males.

beta_male

Scale parameter for the Weibull distribution for males.

delta_male

Location parameter for the Weibull distribution for males.

alpha_female

Shape parameter for the Weibull distribution for females.

beta_female

Scale parameter for the Weibull distribution for females.

delta_female

Location parameter for the Weibull distribution for females.

empirical_density

A density object containing the empirical density of ages.

max_age

Integer, the maximum age considered in the analysis.

Value

The data frame with imputed ages.
